    agedemographics_by_country

    agedemographics_by_country.Rd

    A data frame describing the number of individuals (in thousands) per age group. Age groups span five years, starting with 0-4 years, 5-9 years, etc. with the oldest age group being 100+ years. Columns of the data frame are

    • Index number

    • Variant: type of data in the table row. Mostly estimates

    • Region, subregion, country or area: lists region to which data in the row applies.

    • Notes

    • Country code: three-letter code referring to country or region.

    • Type

    • Parent code

    • Reference data: year of count or estimate

    • 0-4: count (in thousands) of individuals in the age group 0-4.

    • 5-9: count (in thousands) of individuals in the age group 5-9.

    • 10-14: count (in thousands) of individuals in the age group 10-14.

    • 15-19: count (in thousands) of individuals in the age group 15-19.

    • 20-24: count (in thousands) of individuals in the age group 20-24.

    • 25-29: count (in thousands) of individuals in the age group 25-29.

    • 30-34: count (in thousands) of individuals in the age group 30-34.

    • 35-39: count (in thousands) of individuals in the age group 35-39.

    • 40-44: count (in thousands) of individuals in the age group 40-44.

    • 45-49: count (in thousands) of individuals in the age group 45-49.

    • 50-54: count (in thousands) of individuals in the age group 50-54.

    • 55-59: count (in thousands) of individuals in the age group 55-59.

    • 60-64: count (in thousands) of individuals in the age group 60-64.

    • 65-69: count (in thousands) of individuals in the age group 65-69.

    • 70-74: count (in thousands) of individuals in the age group 70-74.

    • 75-79: count (in thousands) of individuals in the age group 75-79.

    • 80-84: count (in thousands) of individuals in the age group 80-84.

    • 85-89: count (in thousands) of individuals in the age group 85-89.

    • 90-94: count (in thousands) of individuals in the age group 90-94.

    • 95-99: count (in thousands) of individuals in the age group 95-99.

    • 100+: count (in thousands) of individuals in the age group 100+.

    Usage

    data(agedemographics_by_country)

    Format

    A dataframe with 29 variables and 18105 observations.

    Source

    UN Department of Economic and Social Affairs: Populations dynamics. World Population Prospects 2019
